snippet: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo builder sentiment index rose this month to its highest level since October 2005, which could lead to a pickup in new home construction.
abstract: National Assn of Home Builders/Wells Fargo builder sentiment index rises to 64 points, up from 61 in September and highest it has been since 2005.
lead_paragraph: The National Association of Home Builders/Wells Fargo builder sentiment index rose this month to its highest level since October 2005, which could lead to a pickup in new home construction.

headline.main: Homebuilders’ Optimism Bodes Well for U.S. Economy
headline.print_headline: Business Briefing; U.S. Home Builders Report Highest Confidence in a Decade
